HEADWORD: Tubulation
<hw>Tu`bu*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>The act of shaping or making a tube, or of providing with a tube;
also, a tube or tubulure; <as>as, the <ex>tubulation</ex> of a
retort</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tubulature</ent>⟦br⟧
